title: Tootie's March 2014 Mix
description:
Tootie's first personal music mix that is simultaneously released on the internet comes a month after his 2/22/14 party and while on the heels of Greg's 40th Birthday Party. A recent addition of significant amounts of "hip" music to his collection shows in this mix.

    Sub Focus - Could This Be Real
    Eiffel 65 - Dub in Life
    Cyndi Lauper - Girls Just Want to Have Fun
    Robert Palmer - I Didn't Mean to Turn You On
    Roxette - It Must Have Been Love
    Florida Georgia Line - Get Your Shine On
    Meat Loaf feat. Ellen Foley - Paradise by the Dashboard Light
    Chicago - 25 or 6 to 4
    Survivor - Burning Heart
    Metallica - I Disappear
    Korn - Hey Daddy
    Limp Bizkit - Nookie
    PFV - SnapShot*
    YG feat. Young Jeezy & Rich Homie Quan - My Nigga
    Fabolous - Keepin it Gangsta
    Waka Flocka Flame feat. Roscoe Dash & Wale - No Hands
    Yung Joc - Do Ya Bad
    Katy Perry feat. Juicy J - Dark Horse
    Kid Ink feat. Tyga - Iz U Down
    Flo Rida feat. will.i.am - In the Ayer
    Jason Derulo feat. 2 Chainz - Talk Dirty (Tootie Uncensored Edit)^

*Track is from lossy source or lossless source with discernible native lossy artifacts
^Portions from lossy source

All tracks are sourced from lossless material unless noted. All of the compilations' songs utilize playback gain values from Tootie's personal volume-leveling procedure, resulting in a consistent overall listening experience without the need to adjust the volume between songs. The method focuses on vocal volume.

Details:
Format: FLAC, level 7
Length: 1 hour, 23 minutes, 23 seconds
Average bitrate: 865 kbps
Embedded CUE Sheet

Playback verified with foobar2000.


Notes:
Produced to be overburned to an 80-minute CD-R.
The use of the tracks in the compilation independently is not recommended as most tracks are intermixed in some way. Some are shortened.
